---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="What is Agentic Ops?" description="Agentic Ops is the next evolution of revenue operations — deploying autonomous AI agents across the GTM stack.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-mesh-hero relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="gradient-orb-lg" style="width: 800px; height: 800px; top: -300px; right: -200px;"></div>
    <div class="container-wide relative z-10 pt-24 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-28">
      <div class="max-w-3xl animate-fade-in">
        <p class="text-label mb-6" style="color: var(--color-accent);">The Manifesto</p>
        <h1 class="text-display text-balance mb-8">
          What is<br />
          <span class="text-gradient">Agentic Ops</span>?
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-ink-light leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
          RevOps gave us workflows, integrations, and dashboards. It was a leap forward.
          But the next leap isn't more automation — it's <strong class="text-ink">autonomy</strong>. That's Agentic Ops.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-separator-accent mx-auto"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Section -->
  <section class="section relative">
    <div class="container-narrow reveal-on-scroll">
      <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-8 text-balance">The problem with RevOps today</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          RevOps was born from a real need: align sales, marketing, and customer success
          around shared data and processes. It worked. We got cleaner CRMs, better reporting,
          and automated handoffs.
        </p>
        <p>
          But here's the thing nobody talks about: most RevOps teams are drowning. They're
          buried in ticket queues, data hygiene tasks, manual enrichment, report building,
          and integration maintenance. The workflows they built created more work, not less.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gradient transition: light to dark -->
  <div class="h-20 md:h-24" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-cream), var(--color-dark));"></div>

  <!-- Key Stat / Pull Quote — Dark section -->
  <section class="section-dark bg-mesh-dark pattern-dots-dark relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="gradient-orb" style="width: 400px; height: 400px; top: -100px; left: -100px;"></div>
    <div class="container-md relative z-10 section text-center">
      <div class="reveal-on-scroll">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-3xl font-serif leading-snug text-balance" style="color: var(--color-cream);">
          The average RevOps professional spends the majority of their time on tasks that are
          repetitive, rule-based, and — critically —
          <span class="text-gradient">delegatable to an AI agent</span>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gradient transition: dark to light -->
  <div class="h-20 md:h-24" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-dark), var(--color-cream));"></div>

  <!-- What Changes Section -->
  <section class="section relative">
    <div class="gradient-orb-lg" style="width: 500px; height: 500px; top: -200px; right: -200px;"></div>
    <div class="container-narrow relative z-10 reveal-on-scroll">
      <div class="accent-bar-wide mb-8"></div>
      <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-8 text-balance">What changes with Agentic Ops</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Agentic Ops is a simple shift in mindset: instead of building workflows that
          <em>humans execute</em>, you deploy agents that <em>execute autonomously</em>
          while humans supervise and strategize.
        </p>
        <p>
          This isn't about "using AI" in the vague way everyone claims to. This is about
          deploying discrete, purpose-built AI agents — using tools like Claude, Relevance AI,
          and custom-built systems — that handle specific GTM functions end-to-end.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Blockquote — Gradient border card technique -->
  <section class="section-gradient-warm relative">
    <div class="container-md section reveal-on-scroll">
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-px" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent), #F59E0B, var(--color-border));">
        <div class="card-glass rounded-2xl p-10 md:p-14 text-center" style="border: none;">
          <svg class="mx-auto mb-6 opacity-20" width="48" height="48" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
            <path d="M14.017 21v-7.391c0-5.704 3.731-9.57 8.983-10.609l.995 2.151c-2.432.917-3.995 3.638-3.995 5.849h4v10h-9.983zm-14.017 0v-7.391c0-5.704 3.748-9.57 9-10.609l.996 2.151c-2.433.917-3.996 3.638-3.996 5.849h3.983v10h-9.983z"/>
          </svg>
          <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif leading-snug text-ink text-balance">
            The best RevOps teams won't be the ones with the most automations. They'll be the ones who deploy the <span class="text-gradient">best agents</span>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gradient transition: light to dark -->
  <div class="h-20 md:h-24" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-cream), var(--color-dark));"></div>

  <!-- Four Layers Section — Dark -->
  <section class="section-dark bg-mesh-dark relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="gradient-orb" style="width: 300px; height: 300px; bottom: 0; right: 10%;"></div>
    <div class="container-md relative z-10 section-lg">
      <div class="reveal-on-scroll mb-12">
        <p class="text-label mb-4">The Stack</p>
        <h2 class="text-display-sm text-balance">The four layers of the Agentic GTM Stack</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mt-4" style="color: #b0b0b0; max-width: 600px;">
          Every GTM operation can be broken into four agent-addressable layers:
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 stagger-children">
        <div class="rounded-2xl p-px hover-lift reveal-on-scroll" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(217,119,6,0.3), rgba(245,158,11,0.15), var(--color-dark-border));">
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 h-full" style="background: var(--color-dark-surface);">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-amber-500/10 border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium" style="color: var(--color-accent);">P</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif" style="color: var(--color-cream);">Prospecting Agents</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="color: #b0b0b0;">Find, qualify, and prioritize leads. Build lists, research accounts, identify buying signals. No more manual prospecting.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl p-px hover-lift reveal-on-scroll" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59,130,246,0.3), rgba(59,130,246,0.1), var(--color-dark-border));">
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 h-full" style="background: var(--color-dark-surface);">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-blue-500/10 border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium" style="color: var(--color-accent);">E</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif" style="color: var(--color-cream);">Enrichment Agents</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="color: #b0b0b0;">Clean, enrich, deduplicate, route, and score data across your CRM and data warehouse. Always running, always current.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl p-px hover-lift reveal-on-scroll" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(16,185,129,0.3), rgba(16,185,129,0.1), var(--color-dark-border));">
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 h-full" style="background: var(--color-dark-surface);">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-emerald-500/10 border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium" style="color: var(--color-accent);">C</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif" style="color: var(--color-cream);">Content Agents</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="color: #b0b0b0;">Draft personalized outreach, create follow-up sequences, generate reports and summaries. Human-quality output at machine scale.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-2xl p-px hover-lift reveal-on-scroll" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(139,92,246,0.3), rgba(139,92,246,0.1), var(--color-dark-border));">
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 h-full" style="background: var(--color-dark-surface);">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-purple-500/10 border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium" style="color: var(--color-accent);">R</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif" style="color: var(--color-cream);">Reporting Agents</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="color: #b0b0b0;">Pull data, surface anomalies, build dashboards, and deliver insights proactively. Analytics that come to you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-10 reveal-on-scroll">
        <a href="/agent-stack" class="btn btn-gradient btn-glow btn-lg">
          Explore the full Agent Stack
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gradient transition: dark to light -->
  <div class="h-20 md:h-24" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-dark), var(--color-cream));"></div>

  <!-- Why Now Section -->
  <section class="section relative">
    <div class="container-narrow relative z-10 reveal-on-scroll">
      <div class="accent-bar-wide mb-8"></div>
      <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-8 text-balance">Why now?</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Three things converged to make Agentic Ops possible:</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 mt-8">
        <div class="card-glow p-6 rounded-2xl">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl font-serif text-gradient leading-none">01</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2">Foundation models got good enough</h3>
              <p class="text-ink-light">Claude, GPT-4, and others can now handle nuanced business tasks — not just chat, but actual execution with judgment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-glow p-6 rounded-2xl">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl font-serif text-gradient leading-none">02</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2">Agent frameworks matured</h3>
              <p class="text-ink-light">Tools like Relevance AI, LangChain, and custom agent architectures make it practical to deploy agents without a PhD in ML.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-glow p-6 rounded-2xl">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl font-serif text-gradient leading-none">03</span>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-serif mb-2">The economics work</h3>
              <p class="text-ink-light">An agent that runs 24/7 costs a fraction of the human hours it replaces. The ROI isn't theoretical anymore — I've seen it firsthand.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who This Is For — Warm gradient background -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-warm pattern-dots-sparse relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container-narrow section reveal-on-scroll">
      <div class="section-separator-accent mb-8"></div>
      <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-8 text-balance">Who this is for</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Agentic Ops isn't for everyone yet. It's for the operators who are already comfortable
          with RevOps fundamentals and are ready to push into the next frontier. If you're still
          figuring out your CRM hygiene basics, do that first.
        </p>
        <p>
          But if you're the kind of person who looks at a manual process and thinks
          "an agent could do this" — you're in the right place.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Where to Start -->
  <section class="section relative">
    <div class="container-narrow relative z-10 reveal-on-scroll">
      <div class="accent-bar-wide mb-8"></div>
      <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-8 text-balance">Where to start</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Start with one agent. Pick your most repetitive, time-consuming GTM task. Build an agent
          that handles 80% of it. Supervise it for a week. Iterate. Then move to the next one.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's the Agentic Ops playbook: <strong>deploy, supervise, iterate, expand.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gradient transition: light to dark -->
  <div class="h-20 md:h-24" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--color-cream), var(--color-dark));"></div>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="section-dark bg-mesh-dark relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="gradient-orb-lg" style="width: 600px; height: 600px; top: -200px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);"></div>
    <div class="container-md relative z-10 section text-center">
      <div class="reveal-on-scroll">
        <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-6">
          Want the <span class="text-gradient">playbooks</span>?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg max-w-lg mx-auto mb-10" style="color: #b0b0b0;">
          I share agent deployment frameworks, tool reviews, and real operator logs every week in the Agentic Ops newsletter.
        </p>
        <div class="max-w-md mx-auto">
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-px" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(217,119,6,0.4), rgba(245,158,11,0.2), var(--color-dark-border));">
            <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background: var(--color-dark-surface);">
              <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
                <input
                  type="email"
                  placeholder="you@company.com"
                  class="flex-1 px-4 py-3 border border-white/10 rounded-lg text-sm text-cream focus:outline-none focus:border-accent focus:ring-1 focus:ring-accent transition-colors"
                  style="background: var(--color-dark);"
                />
                <button class="btn btn-gradient btn-glow">
                  Subscribe
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
